    "chemicalDescription": [
      "r-(Oligopeptide-126 sh-Polypeptide-51 Dipeptide-19 Hexapeptide-40) is a single chain recombinant peptide, produced by fermentation in E. coli. The starting gene is synthesized by the fusion of the genes encoding for Oligopeptide-126, sh-Polypeptide-51, Dipeptide-19 and Hexapeptide-40. The fusion peptide contains 246 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
